straighten /ˈstreɪtən/

(straightening,straightened,straightens) 

1. V-T If you straighten something, you make it neat or put it in its proper position. 整理; 摆好 

例： She sipped her coffee and straightened a picture on the wall. 她抿了口咖啡，然后把墙上的一幅画扶正。 

2. PHRASAL VERB Straighten up means the same as . 整理; 摆好 

例： This is my job, to straighten up, to file things. 这就是我的工作，整理东西，把东西归档。 

3. V-I If you are standing in a relaxed or slightly bent position and then you straighten , you make your back or body straight and upright. 挺直腰 

例： The three men straightened and stood waiting. 那3个人挺直了腰站着等。 

4. PHRASAL VERB Straighten up means the same as . 挺直腰 

例： He straightened up and slipped his hands in his pockets. 他挺直腰，把双手插进衣兜里。 

5. V-T/V-I If you straighten something, or it straightens , it becomes straight. 使变直; 变直 

例： Straighten both legs until they are fully extended. 使双腿挺直，直到他们完全伸展开。 

6. PHRASAL VERB Straighten out means the same as . 使变直; 变直 

例： No one would dream of straightening out the church's knobbly spire. 没人会梦想使教堂的圆形尖顶变直。

